[2] Stavropol
Date: Wed, 5 Nov 2008
Source: RIA Novosti [edited]
<http://en.rian.ru/russia/20081105/118137055.html>


[ProMED-mail apologizes for the delay in posting the below
information. It was a victim of cyberspace challenges. - Mod.MPP]


Swine fever confirmed in another south Russian region
-----------------------------------------------------
The African swine fever virus (ASFV) has spread to a 4th region in
Russia's southern Stavropol Territory, the region's chief vet said on
Wednesday [5 Nov 2008].

Vets have already begun culling pigs in the Yutsa village which has
been affected by the virus. Over 11 000 pigs have already been killed
in the area following the recent outbreak.

Experts say that pork from the culled animals can be consumed once it
has been correctly processed.

5000 pigs were culled or died from the virus this summer in Russia's
North Caucasus republic of North Ossetia.

The virus does not pose a threat to humans.

--
